<P><CASEREF CCDBNUM="1372181">
<SOC>B.C.R. Construction Inc. v. Humphrey</SOC>
<CITE>2013 ONSC 751</CITE>
<CORRELAT>
<CITE>2013 CarswellOnt 1523</CITE>
</CORRELAT>
<COURTJUR>Ont. S.C.J.</COURTJUR>
<CASEHIST>
<CASEDISP>reversed in part</CASEDISP>
<CASEREF CCDBNUM="1574211">
<CITE>2014 ONSC 5576</CITE>
<CORRELAT>
<CITE>2014 CarswellOnt 17175</CITE>
</CORRELAT>
<CORRELAT>
<CITE>45 C.L.R. (4th) 39</CITE>
</CORRELAT>
<CORRELAT>
<CITE>330 O.A.C. 44</CITE>
</CORRELAT>
<COURTJUR>Ont. Div. Ct.</COURTJUR>
</CASEREF>
</CASEHIST>
</CASEREF></P>
<P>The Court held that, despite the outer form, in substance the construction
contract was not independent of the contract for the purchase and sale of lots.</P>
</FREEFORM>
