</CASEREF></P>
<P>If one interprets the words &ldquo;gift card&rdquo; and &ldquo;gift card
agreement&rdquo; in the grammatical and ordinary sense harmoniously with the
scheme of the overall CPA, the object of the CPA and the intention of the
legislature, the words mean cash-equivalent credits or vouchers that are
purchased as gifts for third parties and not simply for personal consumption.</P>
<P><CASEREF CCDBNUM="1658938">
<SOC>Sankar v. Bell Mobility Inc.</SOC>
<CITE>2016 ONCA 242</CITE>
<CORRELAT>
